# Start of question: correct expression for wave of specified omega and k [2]
:TYPE:MC:1:0:C
:TITLE:correct expression for wave of specified omega and k [2]
:FEEDBACK:H

:QUESTION:H
Which of the following expressions represents a wave moving in the positive x direction with a wavenumber of 2.0 m<sup>-1</sup> and an angular frequency of 0.5 s<sup>-1</sup>?
:IMAGE:
:LAYOUT:vertical
:ANSWERORDER:randomized
:INDICES:letters
:ANSWER1:100:H
y(x,t) = (3 cm)sin[(2.0 m<sup>-1</sup>)x - (0.5 s<sup>-1</sup>)t]
:ANSWER2:0:H
y(x,t) = (3 cm)sin[2<FONT FACE="symbol">p</FONT>(2.0 m<sup>-1</sup>)x - 2<FONT FACE="symbol">p</FONT>(0.5 s<sup>-1</sup>)t]
:ANSWER3:0:H
y(x,t) = (3 cm)sin[2<FONT FACE="symbol">p</FONT>/(2.0 m<sup>-1</sup>)x - 2<FONT FACE="symbol">p</FONT>/(0.5 s<sup>-1</sup>)t]
:ANSWER4:0:H
y(x,t) = (3 cm)sin[(0.5 m<sup>-1</sup>)x + (2.0 s<sup>-1</sup>)t]
:CAT:1-D Waves
:Used By1:3183398896
:Used By3:3183398896
# End of question: correct expression for wave of specified omega and k [2]

